narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: If you are interested in the French language then I would recommend taking this course. It is a little advanced.

This class is a lot like L1/L2, but with reading in addition to the usual slate of worksheets and oral exercises. It's a lot of work (probably about 10 hours a week), but Madame Jensen is really nice and helpful. I enjoyed coming to class everyday, much thanks to her work, even though I didn't particularly enjoy the assignments.
Absolutely. This class is a lot of work, but the more input, obviously the more you improve your language skills.
A lot of work. If you put in the work, you can succeed. But if you do not know french going in, don't take it
